 are the onsite Coulomb\nrepulsion and the nearest neighbor hopping, respectively, in the Hamiltonians.\n(II) A universal scaling $T_{c}^{\\rm opt}\\sim 0.16 \\lvert t_1 \\rvert F_{\\rm\nSC}$ holds. (III) SC is enhanced and optimized if $U$ is increased beyond the\nreal available materials. It is further enhanced by decreasing the offsite\ninteraction. The present findings provide useful clues for the design of new SC\nmaterials with even higher $T_{c}^{\\rm opt}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Mar 2023 14:26:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-14"}
